# Feishu wiki scraping (ht-dev-docs)

When re-scraping or updating docs from `lingdongfangcheng.feishu.cn/wiki/`:

1. **Always enter the wiki via the hub URL first**, then **click** to the target article. **Do not** `browser_navigate` straight to inner `wiki/{token}` URLs — that usually triggers **login**. Hub: `https://lingdongfangcheng.feishu.cn/wiki/KOa3wfI8Aiv3xxkmWsrchBPBn5d` (see skill **Wiki entry URL**).

2. **If login/captcha appears:** ask the human to paste the **hub URL** in the Playwright address bar, **click through** to the target page, complete any auth by hand, then reply **`continue`**. Wait for **`continue`**, snapshot, confirm the **target** article URL, then extract. Details: **`.claude/skills/scrape-wiki/SKILL.md`**.

3. **Otherwise** you may use **clicks and typing** in the MCP browser (`browser_click`, `browser_type`, … on **Playwright** `project-0-ht-dev-docs-playwright` or **Cursor IDE Browser** `cursor-ide-browser`). Follow IDE-browser **lock → interact → unlock** when using `cursor-ide-browser`.

4. **External desktop browser login does not help** the isolated MCP session.

5. **Prefer the Docx `client_vars` API** (same Playwright session, `page.request.get` or in-page `fetch` + credentials) over DOM scroll when scraping normal wiki articles — see **Extraction strategy: API first** in **`.claude/skills/scrape-wiki/SKILL.md`**. Fall back to scroll + `[data-block-id]` if the API fails.

6. **Full wiki refresh without MCP:** **`npm run feishu:pull`** then **`npm run feishu:dump_to_markdown`** (or **`npm run feishu:scrape`** for both) — see **End-to-end: two-phase CN wiki workflow** and **`scripts/README.md`**.

7. **Run scroll/extract only after** the article is visible (e.g. **`.bear-web-x-container`**) when using the DOM path. If extraction is empty, assume wrong page, not “empty wiki”.

8. **Full procedure:** **`.claude/skills/scrape-wiki/SKILL.md`**
